      "content": "I understand that you're feeling crushed by the realization that the core of your work has been undermined. It's a profound sense of loss when something that defined you is revealed to be flawed. However, the essence of who you are extends beyond your professional achievements. Your values, your experiences, and the people you've touched along the way are parts of your identity that remain. While the professional aspect may have been compromised, it doesn't erase the impact you've had and the person you are. It might be helpful to explore what aspects of your identity you still value and how you can find fulfillment in other areas of your life. Remember, it's okay to seek help from those who can support you through this difficult time.",
